      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the issues were fixed by cleaning up the minijail invocations. The end result was better sandboxing for each of these other processes so that is good.\n\nRecently dlcservice introduced a similar mount cloning issue. Here the symptom is autoclean loop devices that remain active to serve the cloned loop mounts. See crbug.com/1123529, b/164027725, and also got mixed into b/165165074. (A rough pass at a fix on crrev.com/c/2389360 but it needs input from the DLC folks.)\n\nIf everyone just always used --profile and specified the required paths I would be happiest of all. But I expect we will have new cases periodically.",
      "parentUuid": "4f2d2e16_9b5c1e76",
      "revId": "8f410f13cc8b729574e647f080631226351c0b92",
